e way in the Swiss Alps and Appalachia. His keen reportorial eye treats us to in-depth portraits of musicians from platinum-selling legend Peter Frampton to a devout Christian who spends his days alone in a storage unit bashing away on one of the largest drum sets in the world. Rowell illuminates the feelings that both spur music’s creation and emerge from its performance, as well as the physical instruments that enables their expression. With an uncommon sensitivity and grace, he charts the pleasure and pain of musicians consumed with what they do—as all of us listen in.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aMusical instrumentsvAnecdotes. 0aMusical instruments-Anecdotes. 0aMusiciansvAnecdotes. 0aMusicians-Anecdotes. 0aRock musiciansvAnecdotes. 0aRock musicians-Anecdotes. 7aMUSIC / General.2bisacsh  aGrand Ole Opry.  aHammond organ.  aPeter Frampton.  adrummer.  ainstruments.  amusic making.  amusic.  amusical genres.  amusician.  atalk box.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311071194340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226608938423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226608938/original  a978-3-11-071194-3  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles